<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-07T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2389a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MLB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-07T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>48. Please report in detail as to operations of British submarines in
                                the Baltic, including the kind of warning given to merchant vessels,
                                the care taken of passengers and crew, whether visit and search was
                                carried out, etc.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>